			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Mez Fade trick<a name="72236"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 20 05 10:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi, I thought of this trick that I havent seen mentioned before and I thought you guys might find it useful.  This is done in conjunction with another toon, probably one that cant fade or FD.  
<br />

<br />
As you all probably know, getting mezzed is essentially a mem wipe for NPCs.  This can be used to get friends/boxes to places they wouldnt be able to without fade. 
<br />

<br />
I did this with a pally friend of mine to get his VT key frame from AR.  First I had him take off a few pieces of his MR gear, to ensure my mez will land.  Then we selo up outside AR and go inside.  We both start running towards the back right away and duel each other on the run.  When we reach the podium thingie, I had the pally stand in a relatively safe spot while I mezzed him.  When it landed, i pulled the train out of the room so he wont get reaggroed when the mez broke.  I could then run the train far away, run back and fade.  It took us 3 tries, but worked like a charm.
<br />

<br />
I've used this trick with the same pally to save both our lives several times afterwards.  Mainly deep in dungeons, like The Hole or Old Sebilis.  I haven't seen anyone else mention this trick before, so I'm taking credit for it <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> Anyway, one of you guys can probably think of a better name for it.
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah, there was another trick I thought about, but havent been able to find a use for it yet.  This one involves mezzing too, but in a different way.  
<br />

<br />
I was thinking you could duel someone and mez them and use the mez push to get them through a hostile area.  This might be useful to get a mage through a room to CoH or cleric in to rez.  It's slow but works, if only I could find a place to use it that wasnt easier to just clear the room and walk through &gt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
Also, remember that if you keep the mez song pulsing, you can keep mezzing them even without line of sight, as long as you dont stop the song. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
