				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mez Fade trick<a name="72257"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 20 05 2:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think mem-wipe is a bit confusing term here. What he means is that when you are mezzed, NPCs can no longer attack you, so it is like a memory wipe. This is different from the percent chance to mem-wipe that some mezzes have built in. That attempts to wipe the target of the mezz, not those aggroed on the mezzed player.
<br />

<br />
This was part of the change that stopped pets from breaking mezz. If you are mezzed, they will lose interest and wander off. My shaman survived a wipe in SG that way once. He stood there mezzed while they wiped the group then left him standing there.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
