				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mez Fade trick<a name="72620"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 05 7:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Use the mez push to go through locked doors.  Thats how i got to VoTS camp in ssra.  Grab random mob, damage it to 95%, then mez and push it thru the wall.  Let mez drop, and you are summoned.  Re-mez it, push it back through the wall, and hit fade.
<br />

<br />
You can also do this with /duel'ed players, allowing you to CoH into rooms not normally allowed.
<br />

<br />
As for using it as a now aggro way to position a person in a room, here goes.
<br />

<br />
Mez person A, keep them hosed/tashed/maloed, etc.  Push them.  As long as mez does not fade, the server treats them as an NPC with NO faction.  Mobs won't attack, because they don't really exist.  Same reason you don't get aggro when you are charmed and run past a group of mobs.  When the mez fades, if you are in aggro range, aggro is reestablished, if not in range, no harm/no foul.  Since they never gained aggro, mobs don't know they are there, and hence have no reason to attack.
<br />

<br />
You can do the same thing to pull a mob to you from a group of mobs.  5 mobs sit next to each other, they cant be split, for whatever reason.  Mez closest one and hit fade.  You get initial assist aggro, which drops when you fade.  mobs stop and you mob is slowly pulled to you.  As long as you don't get a resist, and hence reaggro your mezzed mob, it will come to you without reaggroing his friends.
<br />

<br />
Rappa
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
